(firstQuint)Intraperitoneal Aerosol High-pressure Chemotherapy for Women With Recurrent Ovarian Cancer.

 This study aims to investigate the therapeutic efficacy of PIPAC using doxorubicin and cisplatin in women with recurrent ovarian cancer and disease progression with peritoneal carcinomatosis.

 The primary objective of this study is to determine the Clinical Benefit Rate (CBR) according to RECIST criteria after three cycles of PIPAC with cisplatin and doxorubicin.

